The paper deals with software project management and effort estimation, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The proposed model uses machine learning techniques such as support vector machines and neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of environmental factors to predict productivity, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY) research. Finally, the paper uses historical data to train and validate the model, which is a common practice in neural network (cs.NE) research.
